See also: ‘ax_plot2d’, ‘ax_draw3d’, ‘ax_polar’, ‘draw2d’ ### Function:
ax_polar (expr, [var, min, max])

Plot r(θ) curves in polar coordinates as interactive Plotly.js charts.
Standalone function (like ‘ax_plot2d’).

Calling forms:

   • ‘ax_polar(expr, [θ, min, max], options)’ -- single expression
   • ‘ax_polar([expr_1, ..., expr_n], [θ, min, max], options)’ --
     multiple expressions

1.2.1.7 Examples
................

/* Cardioid */
ax_polar(1 + cos(θ), [θ, 0, 2*%pi])$

/* Rose curve */
ax_polar(sin(3*θ), [θ, 0, 2*%pi], color="red", title="Rose Curve")$

/* Multiple curves */
ax_polar(
  [1 + cos(θ), 1 - cos(θ)],
  [θ, 0, 2*%pi],
  title="Cardioids"
)$

/* Spiral */
ax_polar(θ/10, [θ, 0, 6*%pi], title="Archimedean Spiral")$

