See also: ‘ax_draw2d’, ‘ax_bar’ ### Function: ax_heatmap (z_matrix)

Heatmap visualization.  Use inside ‘ax_draw2d’.

Calling forms:

   • ‘ax_heatmap(z_matrix)’ -- pass a Maxima ‘matrix(...)’ directly
   • ‘ax_heatmap(z_matrix, x_labels, y_labels)’ -- matrix with string
     lists for axis labels
   • ‘ax_heatmap(expr, xvar, xlo, xhi, yvar, ylo, yhi)’ -- symbolic
     expression sampled on a grid

1.4.1.6 Examples
................

/* From a matrix */
ax_draw2d(ax_heatmap(matrix([1,2,3],[4,5,6],[7,8,9])))$

/* With axis labels */
M: matrix([85,90,78],[92,88,95])$
ax_draw2d(
  ax_heatmap(M, ["Math","Science","English"], ["Alice","Bob"]),
  colorscale="Blues", title="Scores"
)$

/* From an expression */
ax_draw2d(
  ax_heatmap(sin(x)*cos(y), x, -%pi, %pi, y, -%pi, %pi),
  colorscale="Hot"
)$

